Package ehextractor

package ehextractor
Contains the highest-level classes responsible for extracting 32-bit exception handling information from programs compiled by the Microsoft Visual C++ compiler, finding functions, logging and checking if a binary can be handled by EHExtractor. Called from both the analyzer and the script.
  • Class
    Description
    EHExtractor
    Highest-level class responsible for extracting MSVC exception handling information from a program.
    EHExtractorAnalyzer
    An analyzer that extracts x86 MSVC exception handling information from programs and writes it to a log file.
    EHExtractorAnalyzer.LogLevelEnum
    Enumerates the available minimum log levels to choose from.
    FunctionUtils
    Utility class for finding functions within a given program.
    Logging
    Class responsible for setting up and managing logging for EHExtractor (both analyzer and script versions).
    ProgramValidator
    Class providing methods to validate if a program can be analyzed by EHExtractor.
    SharedReturnCalls
    This class provides an alternative way to 'run' the "Shared Return Calls" analyzer, which is crucial for resolving calls to thunked functions, such as CxxFrameHandler3.
